The House of Representatives on Wednesday resolved to invite President Muhammadu Buhari to provide detailed explanation on the spate of killings going on in parts of the country.

The lawmakers equally resolved to suspend plenary for three legislative days to show concern about the way Nigerians are killed on daily basis unabated.

The House also said all killer herdsmen should be declared as terrorists, while cattle rearers should be registered.

They also asked relevant committees of the Â House to investigate the matter and report back.

The lawmakers declared vote of no confidence on service chiefs and that they should be removed and be replaced immediately.

The resolutions were sequel to a motion by Mark Gbillah (APC, Benue) on the killings of two priests and 17 others in Benue State on Tuesday.